{
  "id": "HEB.7",
  "bibleId": "de4e12af7f28f599-01",
  "number": "7",
  "bookId": "HEB",
  "reference": "Hebrews 7",
  "copyright": "PUBLIC DOMAIN except in the United Kingdom, where a Crown Copyright applies to printing the KJV. See http://www.cambridge.org/about-us/who-we-are/queens-printers-patent",
  "verseCount": 28,
  "content": [
    {
      "name": "para",
      "type": "tag",
      "attrs": {
        "style": "p"
      },
      "items": [
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "1",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:1"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "1",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "For this Melchisedec, king of Salem, priest of the most high God, who met Abraham returning from the slaughter of the kings, and blessed him; ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.1",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.1"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "2",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:2"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "2",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "To whom also Abraham gave a tenth part of all; first being by interpretation King of righteousness, and after that also King of Salem, which is, King of peace; ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.2",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.2"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "3",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:3"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "3",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Without father, without mother, without descent, having neither beginning of days, nor end of life; but made like unto the Son of God; abideth a priest continually. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.3",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.3"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "4",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:4"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "4",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Now consider how great this man ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.4",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.4"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "was",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "HEB.7.4",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "HEB.7.4"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": ", unto whom even the patriarch Abraham gave the tenth of the spoils. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.4",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.4"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "5",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:5"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "5",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And verily they that are of the sons of Levi, who receive the office of the priesthood, have a commandment to take tithes of the people according to the law, that is, of their brethren, though they come out of the loins of Abraham: ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.5",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.5"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "6",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:6"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "6",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "But he whose descent is not counted from them received tithes of Abraham, and blessed him that had the promises. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.6",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.6"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "7",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:7"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "7",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And without all contradiction the less is blessed of the better. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.7",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.7"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "8",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:8"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "8",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And here men that die receive tithes; but there he ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.8",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.8"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "receiveth them",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "HEB.7.8",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "HEB.7.8"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": ", of whom it is witnessed that he liveth. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.8",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.8"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "9",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:9"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "9",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And as I may so say, Levi also, who receiveth tithes, payed tithes in Abraham. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.9",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.9"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "10",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:10"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "10",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "For he was yet in the loins of his father, when Melchisedec met him. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.10",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.10"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "11",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:11"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "11",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "If therefore perfection were by the Levitical priesthood, (for under it the people received the law,) what further need ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.11",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.11"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "was there",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "HEB.7.11",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "HEB.7.11"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " that another priest should rise after the order of Melchisedec, and not be called after the order of Aaron? ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.11",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.11"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "12",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:12"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "12",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "For the priesthood being changed, there is made of necessity a change also of the law. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.12",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.12"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "13",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:13"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "13",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "For he of whom these things are spoken pertaineth to another tribe, of which no man gave attendance at the altar. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.13",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.13"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "14",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:14"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "14",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "For ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.14",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.14"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "it is",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "HEB.7.14",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "HEB.7.14"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " evident that our Lord sprang out of Juda; of which tribe Moses spake nothing concerning priesthood. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.14",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.14"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "15",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:15"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "15",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And it is yet far more evident: for that after the similitude of Melchisedec there ariseth another priest, ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.15",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.15"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "16",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:16"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "16",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Who is made, not after the law of a carnal commandment, but after the power of an endless life. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.16",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.16"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "17",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:17"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "17",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "For he testifieth, Thou ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.17",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.17"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "art",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "HEB.7.17",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "HEB.7.17"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " a priest for ever after the order of Melchisedec. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.17",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.17"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "18",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:18"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "18",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "For there is verily a disannulling of the commandment going before for the weakness and unprofitableness thereof. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.18",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.18"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "19",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:19"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "19",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "For the law made nothing perfect, but the bringing in of a better hope ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.19",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.19"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "did",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "HEB.7.19",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "HEB.7.19"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "; by the which we draw nigh unto God. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.19",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.19"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "20",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:20"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "20",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And inasmuch as not without an oath ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.20",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.20"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "he was made priest",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "HEB.7.20",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "HEB.7.20"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": ": ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.20",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.20"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "21",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:21"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "21",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "(For those priests were made without an oath; but this with an oath by him that said unto him, The Lord sware and will not repent, Thou ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.21",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.21"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "art",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "HEB.7.21",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "HEB.7.21"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " a priest for ever after the order of Melchisedec:) ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.21",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.21"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "22",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:22"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "22",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "By so much was Jesus made a surety of a better testament. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.22",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.22"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "23",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:23"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "23",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "And they truly were many priests, because they were not suffered to continue by reason of death: ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.23",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.23"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "24",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:24"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "24",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "But this ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.24",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.24"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "man",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "HEB.7.24",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "HEB.7.24"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": ", because he continueth ever, hath an unchangeable priesthood. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.24",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.24"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "25",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:25"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "25",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Wherefore he is able also to save them to the uttermost that come unto God by him, seeing he ever liveth to make intercession for them. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.25",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.25"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "26",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:26"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "26",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "For such an high priest became us, ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.26",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.26"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "who is",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "HEB.7.26",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "HEB.7.26"
                ]
              }
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": " holy, harmless, undefiled, separate from sinners, and made higher than the heavens; ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.26",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.26"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "27",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:27"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "27",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "Who needeth not daily, as those high priests, to offer up sacrifice, first for his own sins, and then for the peopleâ€™s: for this he did once, when he offered up himself. ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.27",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.27"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "verse",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "number": "28",
            "style": "v",
            "sid": "HEB 7:28"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "28",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "text": "For the law maketh men high priests which have infirmity; but the word of the oath, which was since the law, ",
          "type": "text",
          "attrs": {
            "verseId": "HEB.7.28",
            "verseOrgIds": [
              "HEB.7.28"
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "char",
          "type": "tag",
          "attrs": {
            "style": "add"
          },
          "items": [
            {
              "text": "maketh",
              "type": "text",
              "attrs": {
                "verseId": "HEB.7.28",
                "verseOrgIds": [
                  "HEB.7.28"
